    body: "St. Paul's distinction between letter and spirit (2 Corinthians 3:6) became foundational for Catholic exegesis. The 'letter' is not simply the literal sense but a wooden, grace-less reading that misses God's purpose. The 'spirit' is the text read in the light of Christ, the Holy Spirit, and the Church's living tradition. This principle undergirds the patristic development of the four senses of Scripture.",
